},{"label":"1Kg 21:16","book":"1Ki","chapter":21,"verse":16}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:21:12","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"this is what the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" God of Israel says: ‘I am about to bring such a disaster on Jerusalem and Judah that everyone who hears about it will shudder. "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Lit about it, his two ears will tingle; Hb obscure"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 3:11","book":"1Sa","chapter":3,"verse":11,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 19:3","book":"Jer","chapter":19,"verse":3,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Sm 3:11","book":"1Sa","chapter":3,"verse":11},{"label":"Jr 19:3","book":"Jer","chapter":19,"verse":3}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Lit about it, his two ears will tingle; Hb obscure"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:21:13","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"I will stretch over Jerusalem the measuring line used on Samaria and the mason’s level used on the house of Ahab, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 34:11","book":"Isa","chapter":34,"verse":11,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Am 7:7–8","book":"Amo","chapter":7,"verse":7,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" and I will wipe "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 23:27","book":"2Ki","chapter":23,"verse":27,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" Jerusalem clean as one wipes a bowl —wiping it and turning it upside down. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Is 34:11","book":"Isa","chapter":34,"verse":11},{"label":"Am 7:7–8","book":"Amo","chapter":7,"verse":7},{"label":"2Kg 23:27","book":"2Ki","chapter":23,"verse":27}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:21:14","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"I will abandon the remnant "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 19:4","book":"2Ki","chapter":19,"verse":4,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 6:9","book":"Jer","chapter":6,"verse":9,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" of my inheritance and hand them over to their enemies. They will become plunder and spoil to all their enemies, "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 19:4","book":"2Ki","chapter":19,"verse":4},{"label":"Jr 6:9","book":"Jer","chapter":6,"verse":9}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:21:15","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"because they have done what is evil in my sight and have angered me from the day their ancestors came out of Egypt until today.’” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 32:22","book":"Exo","chapter":32,"verse":22,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 25:7","book":"Jer","chapter":25,"verse":7,"letter":"b"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ex 32:22","book":"Exo","chapter":32,"verse":22},{"label":"Jr 25:7","book":"Jer","chapter":25,"verse":7}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:21:16","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Manasseh also shed so much innocent blood that he filled Jerusalem with it from one end to another. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 24:4","book":"2Ki","chapter":24,"verse":4,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" This was in addition to his sin that he caused Judah to commit, so that they did what was evil in the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"’s sight."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 24:4","book":"2Ki","chapter":24,"verse":4}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:21:17","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The rest "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 33:18–20","book":"2Ch","chapter":33,"verse":18,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" of the events of Manasseh’s reign, along with all his accomplishments and the sin that he committed, are written in the Historical Record of Judah’s Kings. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 20:20","book":"2Ki","chapter":20,"verse":20,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Ch 33:18–20","book":"2Ch","chapter":33,"verse":18},{"label":"2Kg 20:20","book":"2Ki","chapter":20,"verse":20}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:21:18","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Manasseh rested with his ancestors and was buried in the garden of his own house, the garden of Uzza. His son Amon became king in his place."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:21:19","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Amon was twenty-two years old when he became king, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 33:21–25","book":"2Ch","chapter":33,"verse":21,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" and he reigned two years in Jerusalem. His mother’s name was Meshullemeth daughter of Haruz; she was from Jotbah. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Ch 33:21–25","book":"2Ch","chapter":33,"verse":21}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:21:20","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He did what was evil in the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"’s sight, just as his father Manasseh had done. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 21:2","book":"2Ki","chapter":21,"verse":2,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 21:11","book":"2Ki","chapter":21,"verse":11,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 21:16","book":"2Ki","chapter":21,"verse":16,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 21:2","book":"2Ki","chapter":21,"verse":2},{"label":"2Kg 21:11","book":"2Ki","chapter":21,"verse":11},{"label":"2Kg 21:16","book":"2Ki","chapter":21,"verse":16}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:21:21","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He walked in all the ways his father had walked; he served the idols his father had served, and he bowed in worship to them. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 16:2","book":"2Ki","chapter":16,"verse":2,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 16:2","book":"2Ki","chapter":16,"verse":2}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:21:22","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He abandoned the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" God of his ancestors "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 11:33","book":"1Ki","chapter":11,"verse":33,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" and did not walk in the ways of the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":". "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 22:17","book":"2Ki","chapter":22,"verse":17,"letter":"b"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 11:33","book":"1Ki","chapter":11,"verse":33},{"label":"2Kg 22:17","book":"2Ki","chapter":22,"verse":17}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:21:23","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Amon’s servants conspired against him and put the king to death in his own house. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 12:20","book":"2Ki","chapter":12,"verse":20,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 14:19","book":"2Ki","chapter":14,"verse":19,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 12:20","book":"2Ki","chapter":12,"verse":20},{"label":"2Kg 14:19","book":"2Ki","chapter":14,"verse":19}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:21:24","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The common people "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Lit The people of the land"},{"kind":"text","text":" killed "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 14:5","book":"2Ki","chapter":14,"verse":5,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" all who had conspired against King Amon, and they made his son Josiah "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 22:1","book":"2Ki","chapter":22,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" king in his place."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 14:5","book":"2Ki","chapter":14,"verse":5},{"label":"2Kg 22:1","book":"2Ki","chapter":22,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Lit The people of the land"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:21:25","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The rest of the events of Amon’s reign, along with his accomplishments, are written in the Historical Record of Judah’s Kings. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:21:26","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He was buried in his tomb in the garden of Uzza, and his son Josiah became king in his place."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]}]},"cachedAt":1783279424144}